<paragraph id="1E2DAB0A8D33C719DCBCFA4DF5FF0F99" blockId="4.[136,1452,1414,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DCBCFA4DF41C0CDD" bold="true" box="[189,325,1414,1440]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Discussion:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DD60FA4CF7560CDD" authorityName="Hamzaoglu &amp; Koc" authorityYear="2022" box="[353,527,1414,1440]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zaferi">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DD60FA4CF7560CDD" box="[353,527,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Hesperis zaferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DEB0FA4CF6130CDD" authorityName="A. Duran (Duran &amp; Cetin" authorityYear="2016" box="[689,842,1415,1440]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tosyaensis">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DEB0FA4CF6130CDD" box="[689,842,1415,1440]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. tosyaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DF89FA4CF1520CDD" authorityName="A. Duran" authorityYear="2009" box="[904,1035,1414,1440]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ozcelikii">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DF89FA4CF1520CDD" box="[904,1035,1414,1440]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. ozcelikii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in habit, inflorescence and siliquae measurements (
<bibRefCitation id="7A03D6FB8D33C719DD38FA61F48B0CB9" author="Dvorak, F." box="[313,466,1450,1476]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" pagination="259 - 271" refId="ref5113" refString="Dvorak, F. (1973) Infrageneric classification of Hesperis L. Feddes Repertorium 84: 259 - 271." type="journal article" year="1973">Dvořák 1973</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7A03D6FB8D33C719DDDEFA60F7300CB9" author="Duran, A." box="[479,617,1450,1477]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" pagination="577 - 584" refId="ref4836" refString="Duran, A. (2009) Hesperis ozcelikii (Brassicaceae), a new species from Turkey. Annales Botanici Fennici 46: 577 - 584." type="journal article" year="2009">Duran 2009</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="7A03D6FB8D33C719DE77FA60F63F0CB8" author="Duran, A. &amp; Cetin, O." box="[630,870,1450,1477]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" pagination="87 - 96" refId="ref5024" refString="Duran, A. &amp; Cetin, O. (2016) New species and a synonym of the genus Hesperis (Brassicaceae) from Turkey. Turkish Journal of Botany 40: 87 - 96. https: // dx. doi. org / 10.3906 / bot- 1407 - 71" type="journal article" year="2016">Duran &amp; Çetin 2016</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DF7BFA60F6920CB9" box="[890,971,1450,1476]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zafe">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DF7BFA60F6920CB9" box="[890,971,1450,1476]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. zafe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
ri is closer in distribution to 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719D915FA60F0F20CB9" authorityName="A. Duran (Duran &amp; Cetin" authorityYear="2016" box="[1300,1451,1451,1476]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tosyaensis">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719D915FA60F0F20CB9" box="[1300,1451,1451,1476]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. tosyaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Tosya, 
<collectingRegion id="DC5665E88D33C719DCE7FA04F4830C94" box="[230,474,1486,1513]" country="Turkey" name="Kastamonu" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Kastamonu Province</collectingRegion>
). The distance as the crow flies between the two species is approximately 
<quantity id="D96A06EF8D33C719D94AFA05F0F10C95" box="[1355,1448,1486,1512]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" unit="km" value="100.0">100 km</quantity>
. However, while 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DD4BFA38F4E80F71" authorityName="Hamzaoglu &amp; Koc" authorityYear="2022" box="[330,433,1522,1548]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zaferi">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DD4BFA38F4E80F71" box="[330,433,1522,1548]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. zaferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<collectingRegion id="DC5665E88D33C719DDC5FA39F74B0F71" box="[452,530,1522,1548]" country="Turkey" name="Corum" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Çorum</collectingRegion>
/ 
<collectingRegion id="DC5665E88D33C719DE1BFA39F7300F71" box="[538,617,1522,1548]" country="Turkey" name="Yozgat" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Yozgat</collectingRegion>
Provinces) is grown in the Irano-Turanian phytogeographic region, 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719D991FA38F5A20F4D" authorityName="A. Duran (Duran &amp; Cetin" authorityYear="2016" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tosyaensis">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719D991FA38F5A20F4D" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. tosyaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, grown at the northwest of it, has adapted to the Euro-Siberian region. 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DFFBF9DCF12E0F4D" authorityName="A. Duran" authorityYear="2009" box="[1018,1143,1558,1584]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="ozcelikii">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DFFBF9DCF12E0F4D" box="[1018,1143,1558,1584]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. ozcelikii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Sütçüler, 
<collectingRegion id="DC5665E88D33C719D8EFF9DCF0FA0F4C" box="[1262,1443,1558,1585]" country="Turkey" name="Isparta" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Isparta Province</collectingRegion>
) shows a distribution in the southwest at approximately 
<quantity id="D96A06EF8D33C719DEF3F9F1F61E0F29" box="[754,839,1594,1620]" metricMagnitude="5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" unit="km" value="400.0">400 km</quantity>
as the crow flies from 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719D848F9F0F1F50F29" authorityName="Hamzaoglu &amp; Koc" authorityYear="2022" box="[1097,1196,1594,1620]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zaferi">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719D848F9F0F1F50F29" box="[1097,1196,1594,1620]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. zaferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and has adapted to the Mediterranean region. Pubescence is the most important characteristic that separates 
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719D845F994F1260F05" box="[1092,1151,1631,1656]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. za</emphasis>
feri from these two similar species. In 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DD09F948F4320FE1" authorityName="Hamzaoglu &amp; Koc" authorityYear="2022" box="[264,363,1666,1692]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zaferi">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DD09F948F4320FE1" box="[264,363,1666,1692]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. zaferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the body and pedicels are bifurcate and stellate, whereas, trifid pubescence is not found on the leaves. Furthermore, the basal and body leaves in 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DEB9F96CF6420FBD" authorityName="Hamzaoglu &amp; Koc" authorityYear="2022" box="[696,795,1702,1728]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="zaferi">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DEB9F96CF6420FBD" box="[696,795,1702,1728]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">H. zaferi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are always entire and the petal claw is clearly short (
<tableCitation id="53109EB18D33C719D96DF96DF5C00F99" captionStart="TABLE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,224,158,182]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="TABLE 2. Diagnostic characters of Hesperis zaferi, H. tosyaensis and H. ozcelikii." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/4AEDFB828D32C718DC89FF55F6A709CA" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" tableUuid="4AEDFB828D32C718DC89FF55F6A709CA">Table 2</tableCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1E2DAB0A8D33C719DCBCF925F6980E9D" blockId="4.[136,1452,1414,2019]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DCBCF925F7900E75" bold="true" box="[189,713,1774,1801]" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">
Specimens Examined:— 
<taxonomicName id="D992D0898D33C719DDE0F925F79B0E75" authorityName="A. Duran (Duran &amp; Cetin" authorityYear="2016" box="[481,706,1774,1800]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Brassicaceae" genus="Hesperis" kingdom="Plantae" order="Brassicales" pageId="4" pageNumber="34" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tosyaensis">
<emphasis id="2CE677188D33C719DDE0F925F79B0E75" bold="true" box="[481,706,1774,1800]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="34">Hesperis tosyaensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
